		President and CEO, 

	
		 Jacobs Engineering Group Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 05/14/2017 



Executive Summary
Demetriou in August 2015 was hired as President and Chief Executive Officer of Jacobs Engineering Group Inc., one of the world’s largest and most diverse providers of professional technical services. Demetriou also became a member of the company’s Board of Directors. Before joining Jacobs Demetriou was Chairman and CEO 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Demetriou is the son of a Boston restaurateur.
Demetriou is the majority owner of the NBA D-league basketball team, the Erie Bayhawks, a NBA Development League team affiliated with the Orlando Magic. 
Current Focus

Company Snapshot: Jacobs Engineering Group Inc. is one of the world’s largest and most diverse providers of professional technical services. The Pasadena, California-based compa 
Biographical Highlights

Born in 1959.
Demetriou earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Chemical Engineering from Tufts University in 1980. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Directors, Noveon (2001 - 2004)
Former Member, Board of Directors, Commonwealth Industries Inc. (2002 - 2004) 
 





